{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 MIDI Probalocity\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Input velocity determines chance of whether note will be passed or blocked.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Full (127) velocity notes will always be passed.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Use Scale and Offset to bring output velocities to the required level.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Scale lowers high velocities. Offset sets the base velocity level.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 http://wiki.cockos.com/wiki/index.php/Jesusonic_Effects_Documentation#Probalocity\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
